         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">October 26th [186]4 ¶ editorial addition. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the rules adopted by the Trustees for the management of the Royal Park. ¶ See M to G. Sprigg, 21 Oct...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.10.26c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Sprigg</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 64/631, unit 4, pp. 108-9, VPRS 2225 outward letterpress copy books, Acclimatisation Society of Victoria, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">October 26th [186]4<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the rules adopted by the Trustees for the management of the Royal Park.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to G. Sprigg, 21 October 1864 (in this edition as 64-10-21b).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Regulations for the management of the Zoological Reserve, Royal Park' were published in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria Government Gazette</seg>, no. 111, 28 October1864, p. 2408.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>These have been laid before the Council who have directed me to request your attention to one or two of the provisions therein contained. In the third rule it is stated that the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>maintenance of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Perimeters will be thrown upon the Society and is to be done at the expense of the Society funds. [This] the Council [imagine] to be an […] as from the condition of the fence a big expenditure will soon be necessary and […] the Council is not in a position to oblige. Hitherto all repairs to the fences have been defrayed out of the […] as directed by the Trustees.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Clause 3 of the Regulations stated 'The Council of the Acclimatization Society will be required to maintain in good repair the boundary fence of the Zoological Reserve, and to defray the cost of repairs and renewals of that fence out of the funds placed at theoir disposal.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will also call your attention to the fifth rule which states that no persons can enter the Park […] if accompanied by dogs and further that persons on horseback will not be permitted to canter on the grass.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Clause 5 of the regulations stated 'The portion of the Zoological Reserve not especially enclosed by the Council of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Acclimatization Society, and used for the depasturing of imported animals and their progeny, shall be open to the public from sunrise to sunset, subject to the condition that the persons admitted to the reserve shall be unaccompanied by dogs, and that if in vehicles or on horseback the roadways not be departed from.'</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Both of these rules<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I fear be found powerless. I would further suggest the addition of a rule prohibiting the kindling of any fire in the Park &amp; the discharging of any fireworks<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also G. Sprigg to M, 2 November<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1864 (in this edition as 64-11-02a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most Obedt Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Geo Sprigg</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secy</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To Dr Mueller F.R.S.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hony Secretary Trustees of Royal Park</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. As soon as the rules are formally proposed I [presume] it will be desirable that they should be printed in […]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">illegible</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— MS water damaged.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">if more than one word say<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; ">two words illegible</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or whatever. Repeat for each […].</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Anything in the minutes re this?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and exhibited at the Park gates.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
